TENNESSEE
By virtue of and pursuant to the authority vested in me as President of the United States, and in order to effectuate further the purposes of the Migratory Bird Conservation Act (45 Stat. 1222), it is ordered that the lands and waters acquired or to be acquired by the United States in the following-described areas in Lake and Obion Counties, Tennessee, be, and they are hereby, reserved and set apart, subject to existing valid rights, for the use of the Department of Agriculture as a refuge and breeding ground for migratory birds and other wildlife:
Provided
, That any private lands within the area described shall become part of the refuge hereby established upon acquisition of title thereto or control thereof by the United States:
